<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 11:56PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Randolph, eastern Fulton and northeastern Sharp Counties through 1230
AM CDT...
At 1156 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mammoth Spring, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cherokee Village...               Highland in Sharp County...
Mammoth Spring...                 Hardy...
Mammoth Spring State Park...      Armstrong...
Fryatt...                         Saddler Falls...
Eleven Point...                   Saddle...
Wirth...                          Ozark Acres...
Elm Store...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
